# AI Courtroom CLI

AI Courtroom CLI is a terminal-only MVP of AI Courtroom. It runs entirely from Python on the command line, stores sessions locally in SQLite, generates a courtroom-style multi-agent debate with mocked responses, and exports verdict reports to Markdown.

## Core capabilities

- create a new decision case from the terminal
- run a structured debate across specialized agents
- store cases, messages, verdicts, reports, and history locally
- print the full debate and verdict in the terminal
- export the final report to Markdown

## Agents included

- Case Intake Agent
- Pro Advocate
- Contra Advocate
- Technical Expert
- Financial Expert
- Skeptic
- Futurist
- Judge

## Architecture goals

- CLI-only workflow
- Python-only MVP with no browser requirement
- storage in SQLite for local persistence
- modular provider interface so real LLM APIs can be added later
- deterministic mock outputs for testing and demos

## Project structure

```text
